==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun|head=[[itinerant]] [[worker]]}}

# {{colloquial|Southern California}} A temporary worker, particularly for exhausting [[manual labor]].
# One who maintains no permanent residence, considered an an itinerant [[http://www.irs.gov/businesses/small/international/article/0,,id=129432,00.html|worker worker]] by the IRS. Such a person is never considered away from home because he has no home to be away from.

